    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So in some situations helper.state is not the one linked to the results events. Here's an example workflow that @bobylito gave me:\n- instantiate\n- helper.state is X\n- call .search() #1\n- refine on smg\n- helper.state is Y\n- => result() event for search #1. helper.state is Y (mismatch), result(data, state) state is X (ok)\n- call .search() #2\n- => result event for search #2. helper.state is Y (ok),  result(data, state) state is Y (ok)\n\nThis is why we should still give the `right` state event in the widgets render(), the helper is doing the work to provide the right state in the result event.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-09-14T12:05:44Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/82#issuecomment-140049953",
    "id": 140049953,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/82",
